	<logo>https://static.globalissues.org/i/globalissues/logo-feed.jpg</logo><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/21/40217</id><title>‘One Earth, One Health’: Yoga Day provides respite in a tumultuous world</title><updated>2025-06-21T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/21/40217" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/21-06-2025_UN_Yoga_Day_2.jpg/image1024x768.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/21-06-2025_UN_Yoga_Day_2.jpg/image1024x768.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In an age marked by conflicts, disease, dysfunction and mental health challenges, yoga offers a steady, time-trusted path to help find calm and harmony within – and without.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/21/40217&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “‘One Earth, One Health’: Yoga Day provides respite in a tumultuous world”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/21-06-2025_UN_Yoga_Day_2.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/21/40216</id><title>UN reiterates call for urgent de-escalation amid Iran-Israel conflict, worsening Gaza crisis</title><updated>2025-06-21T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/21/40216" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Senior UN officials reiterated an appeal for urgent restraint on Saturday as conflict spiral between Israel and Iran, amid a wider regional crisis exacerbated by Israel’s war in Gaza and the worsening humanitarian situation facing Palestinian civilians.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/21/40216&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “UN reiterates call for urgent de-escalation amid Iran-Israel conflict, worsening Gaza crisis”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/21/40215</id><title>From the Global South to the stars: A new space race</title><updated>2025-06-21T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/21/40215" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/19-06-2025-NASA-cyclones.jpg/image1024x768.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/19-06-2025-NASA-cyclones.jpg/image1024x768.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Once the exclusive domain of a handful of technologically advanced countries, outer space is now within the reach of emerging nations from the Global South, as costs fall and technology becomes more widely available.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/21/40215&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “From the Global South to the stars: A new space race”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/19-06-2025-NASA-cyclones.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/21/40214</id><title>Why is the manosphere on the rise? UN Women sounds the alarm over online misogyny</title><updated>2025-06-21T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/21/40214" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/21-02-2023_Unsplash_laptop.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/21-02-2023_Unsplash_laptop.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A growing network of online communities known collectively as the “manosphere” is emerging as a serious threat to gender equality, as toxic digital spaces increasingly influence real-world attitudes, behaviours, and policies, the UN agency dedicated to ending gender discrimination has warned. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/21/40214&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Why is the manosphere on the rise? UN Women sounds the alarm over online misogyny”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/21-02-2023_Unsplash_laptop.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40204</id><title>Climate and Health: Urgent Need for Adaptation Strategies in Africa</title><updated>2025-06-20T11:15:59-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40204" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://static.globalissues.org/ips/2025/06/IMG_2960-629x231.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://static.globalissues.org/ips/2025/06/IMG_2960-629x231.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;BONN, Jun 20 (IPS)  - In recent years, there has been growing evidence of how climate change is impacting human health in several ways.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40204&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Climate and Health: Urgent Need for Adaptation Strategies in Africa”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://static.globalissues.org/ips/2025/06/IMG_2960-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40207</id><title>Women Protestors Targeted, Insulted on Georgian Anti-Government Rallies</title><updated>2025-06-20T09:02:30-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40207" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://static.globalissues.org/ips/2025/06/1000013396-354x472.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://static.globalissues.org/ips/2025/06/1000013396-354x472.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;BRATISLAVA, Jun 20 (IPS)  - Having attended hundreds of anti-government protests in the Georgian capital, Tbilisi, Gvantsa Kalandadze is no stranger to police intimidation and violence.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40207&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Women Protestors Targeted, Insulted on Georgian Anti-Government Rallies”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://static.globalissues.org/ips/2025/06/1000013396-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40213</id><title>Ukraine: Security Council hears of escalating attacks, diplomatic developments</title><updated>2025-06-20T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40213" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/24-04-2025-Kyiv-Ukraine-attacks-08.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/24-04-2025-Kyiv-Ukraine-attacks-08.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The UN Security Council met on Friday to discuss the situation in Ukraine, where intensified fighting continues, affecting new areas and prompting further displacement. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40213&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Ukraine: Security Council hears of escalating attacks, diplomatic developments”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/24-04-2025-Kyiv-Ukraine-attacks-08.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40212</id><title>‘A fire no one can control’: UN warns of spiralling Iran-Israel war</title><updated>2025-06-20T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40212" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/20-06-2025-UN-Photo-Guterres-01.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/20-06-2025-UN-Photo-Guterres-01.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The world stands on the edge of catastrophe, United Nations Secretary-General António Guterres warned on Friday, as Israel’s military campaign inside Iran intensifies and strikes on nuclear facilities threaten to trigger a catastrophe.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40212&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “‘A fire no one can control’: UN warns of spiralling Iran-Israel war”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/20-06-2025-UN-Photo-Guterres-01.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40211</id><title>UN Peacebuilding Commission ‘more needed than ever’ amid rising conflict</title><updated>2025-06-20T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40211" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/08-05-2020-NICA-750383-UNMIL-Chinese-FPU.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/08-05-2020-NICA-750383-UNMIL-Chinese-FPU.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Former Liberian President Ellen Johnson-Sirleaf and other senior officials from across the world have spoken about how international support was critical to putting their countries on the path to peace.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40211&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “UN Peacebuilding Commission ‘more needed than ever’ amid rising conflict”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/08-05-2020-NICA-750383-UNMIL-Chinese-FPU.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40210</id><title>WHO warns of a health financing emergency</title><updated>2025-06-20T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40210" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/28-02-2025-UNAIDS-Tanzania-02.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/28-02-2025-UNAIDS-Tanzania-02.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The world is facing a health financing emergency, according to Dr. Kalipso Chalkidou, Director for Health Financing and Economics for the World Health Organization (WHO).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40210&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “WHO warns of a health financing emergency”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/28-02-2025-UNAIDS-Tanzania-02.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry></feed><!-- 0.0015s -->